The order of 6 parameters of the USER's function YOUNG MODULUS
at time TIME, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
must be

YOUNG( TIME, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJECT, NO_OBJECT ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of the YOUNG MODULUS
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc Young( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then Young= 200E9;
     { Cf. http://www.engineeringtoolbox.com/young-modulus-d_417.html}
     { Pascal or 200 GigaPascal (1GPa=1E9 N/m2) for its YOUNG MODULUS}
     { ELASTICITY only if 
          STRAINS EpsilonE<YR=250*(1E6 N/m2 or MPa) its YIELD STRENGTH and
          STRESSES  SigmaE<SE=400*(1E6 N/m2 or MPa) is its ULTIMATE TENSILE STRENGTH
       are the ELASTICITY-PLASTICITY THRESHOLD }
else if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
     then Young=90e9; {hot-rolled annealed copper}
                      {150e9 for hard annealed copper}
     else Young=0 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc; 

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
